				 <tr>
				  <td>
				    <a name="32">&nbsp;</a><br>
				    <div class="NewsHeadline">Raid Etiquette [a list of things considered bad form]</div>
				  </td>
				 </tr>
				 <tr>
				  <td>
				    <div class="NewsInfo">
					RAID INFO -
					Saturday, June 23, 2001&nbsp;14:48
					by 
					<a class="NewsLink" href="author_profile.asp?name=suki">suki</a>
					<br>
				    
				    </div>
				  </td>
				 </tr>
				 <tr>
				   <td>
				     <div class="NewsText" align="justify">
				       A.] Things raid followers should avoid doing :<br><br>1.] arguing over an open, full-zone, channel about not having gotten an item, not doing a break the way a certain person wanted to, etc.<br>2.] blatant disregard for a raid leader's instructions. [i.e. running left out of spite when one was suppose to go right, not /assisting for sheer malice, refusing to move thereby hindering the progress of the raid]<br>3.] looting of important drops regardless of who they were awarded too [a.k.a. Ninja looting]<br>4.] leaving a raid without informing the raid leader[major NO NO] as this leaves a once safe group vulnerable with out knowing backup is needed... <br>5.] constantly sending a raid leader tells, disturbing his/her efforts to organize and run the raid.<br>6.] showing up late or needing a last minute port, if a fellow raider feels the compassion to leave and get your late butt, that is his decision[to ask from raid leader] and NOT your demand..<br><br>B.] Things raid leaders should avoid doing :<br><br>1.] do not award items only to one's guild or friends in mixed raids. Be fair about the loot.<br>2.] do not leave the raiding area until all other members of the raid have found a way out.<br>3.] don’t get in over your head. Delegate people to do tasks and try to avoid getting overly stressed. It’s a massive job and your raiders need you to be thinking clearly.
				     </div>
				   </td>
				 </tr>		 
				 <tr style="padding-top: 5px">
				   <td>
				     <div class="NewsBar">
				       ( 
				       <!-- <a class="NewsLink" href="news.asp">Back to Newsflash</a> | 
				       <a class="NewsLink" href="mailto:suki@insyracuse.com">Email to Author</a> |  -->
				       
				       <a class="NewsLink" href="comment.asp?IDCategory=48&IDNews=32">0 Comments</a> 
				       )
				     </div>
				   </td>
				 </tr>
