				       I know we all are very good on these things, but wanted to post this as a general standard for all to understand both sides. And mainly those who have NOT lead a raid, have little place critizing those that are trying to organize the current one.. <br>[I will edit/delete this if it is in bad form]<br><br>I feeel that any and all members of echelon are capable of hosting a raid, But not all are leaders, and many are just happy to follow and be told what is needed to do.. Though if you are unsure of your ability to lead, my best advice is to face your fear and trry. start with small pickup groups and use tactical attacks on mobs or locations. try to improve skills and you shall lead a successful raid.. Count on the members of your party or guild to smooth out the weaknessess.
